===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{inh|en|ang|butere||butter}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*buterǭ||butter}} (compare {{cog|fy|buter}}, {{cog|nl|boter}}, {{cog|de|Butter}}), from {{der|en|la|būtȳrum}}, from {{der|en|grc|βούτῡρον||cow cheese}}, compound of {{m|grc|βοῦς||ox, cow}} and {{m|grc|τῡρός||cheese}}, from {{etyl|xsc|en}}.

Compare {{cog|ae|𐬌𐬭𐬌𐬏𐬙||tr=tūiri|curdled milk, whey}}), from {{der|en|ine-pro|*tuHrós}} (compare [[Middle Indic]] {{m|und|tr=tūra|gloss=cheese}}, {{cog|ru|творо́г||curds, soft cheese}}, {{cog|ang|þweran||to churn}}, {{m|ang|geþweor||curds}}).

